<item>
            <title>[LU-19290] kernel update [RHEL 9.6 5.14.0-570.37.1.el9_6]</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-19290</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Security Fix(es) for kernel 5.14.0-570.35.1.el9_6:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;kernel: bpf, test_run: Fix use-after-free issue in eth_skb_pkt_type() (CVE-2025-21867)&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;microcode_ctl: From CVEorg collector (CVE-2024-28956)&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;kernel: mm/hugetlb: unshare page tables during VMA split, not before (CVE-2025-38084)&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;kernel: mm/hugetlb: fix huge_pmd_unshare() vs GUP-fast race (CVE-2025-38085)&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;kernel: net: fix udp gso skb_segment after pull from frag_list (CVE-2025-38124)&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;kernel: wifi: rtw88: fix the &apos;para&apos; buffer size to avoid reading out of bounds (CVE-2025-38159)&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;kernel: Bluetooth: hci_core: Fix use-after-free in vhci_flush() (CVE-2025-38250)&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;kernel: i2c/designware: Fix an initialization issue (CVE-2025-38380)&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;kernel: tls: always refresh the queue when reading sock (CVE-2025-38471)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://access.redhat.com/errata/product/479/ver=/rhel---9/x86_64/RHSA-2025:13962&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://access.redhat.com/errata/product/479/ver=/rhel---9/x86_64/RHSA-2025:13962&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Security Fix(es) for kernel 5.14.0-570.37.1.el9_6:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;kernel: udp: Fix memory accounting leak. (CVE-2025-22058)&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;kernel: net_sched: ets: Fix double list add in class with netem as child qdisc (CVE-2025-37914)&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;kernel: ice: fix eswitch code memory leak in reset scenario (CVE-2025-38417)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://access.redhat.com/errata/product/479/ver=/rhel---9/x86_64/RHSA-2025:14420&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://access.redhat.com/errata/product/479/ver=/rhel---9/x86_64/RHSA-2025:14420&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
